<br>
Is it just me, or do we not have enough room for stuff anymore?<br>
<br>
In my bank, I have 80 slots. That seems like a lot, until I cleaned it out the other day, destroyed a lot of stuff that I (think) I don't need anymore (will turn out to be a rare drop quest item next week, heh), and filled those slots with stuff from Nerun. Then I realized I still didn't have room to put all my tradeskill components and results, which meant constant bag switching while I was doing tradeskills.<br>
<br>
Suddenly, it was full again. Now, I'm not rich, I mostly have quest items in there, a backpack of drop spells, and 2 backpacks of dropped equipment or old nodrop stuff that I can't bring myself to get rid of... mostly stuff awaiting sale or need.<br>
<br>
Sure, I could make a mule, in fact I'm going to have to soon, but I think it's time that Verant upgraded at least our bank, and preferably the char inventory as well. At least make backpacks with more slots!<br>
<br>
I also think they should make it so you can have perhaps 100 items per stack, instead of 20. This would especially apply to spider silks, furs, and other various tradeskill supplies.<br>
<br>
Granted, in real life you wouldn't be able to carry that much, but you would also be able to hire a friggin mule train to carry your stuff!<br>
<br>
I do see how this would be a coding nightmare (especially since I am in software development) but you gotta start talking about it sometime, and that's what I am hoping to start here. I'm going to /feedback it tonight as well.<br>
<br>
I think that some very good steps could be:<br>
<br>
1. Make all stacks max at 99 or 100 (depending on how their code works, 99 may be more feasible) instead of the current 20. This alone would buy a LOT of time to upgrade the rest.<br>
<br>
2. Add room to the bank, it IS a bank after all, or add a mini-storage in each city  heheh<br>
<br>
3. Consider adding 4 more general inventory slots, or increasing backpack slots (maybe to 12?)<br>
<br>
4. Make it so I can have more than 2 backpacks open at once, lol, I hate when I have to have materials/storage for finished result in one bag and have the other open bag slot be monopolized by the combining container. That always leads to a lot of bag switching, which = lag on my lowly P3 500MHz.<br>
<br>
